ADDIS ABABA, Ethiopia, March 13, 2019/APO Group/ --
                                                        
                            The United States Agency for International Development (USAID) Pastoralists Area Resilience Improvement and Market Expansion Project (PRIME), a Feed the Future Initiative, is marking the end of its seven years of assistance to Ethiopia’s pastoralists with a closeout celebration and learning event. State Minister Dr. Seyoum Mesfin from the Ministry of Peace and USAID Mission Director Leslie Reed will deliver remarks at the event, which will gather representatives from the Ministry of Agriculture, Ministry of Health, Ministry of Education, and Ministry of Water, Energy, and Irrigation.



The United States Embassy in Addis Ababa invites you to attend this event.

Date: March 14, 2019 at 9:00 a.m.

Venue: Ethiopian Skylight Hotel, Bole, Addis Ababa

To confirm attendance, please contact David Kahrmann, USAID Senior Development Outreach and Communications Specialist at dkahrmann@usaid.gov.